The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Timeout

 art

 Till September 3 at Idiyas Gallery, 15 Dover Road; 10.30 am - 7.30 pm: Autumn Bloom, showcasing works of well-known artists. 

 Till September 3 at Gallery Sanskriti, 5C Alipore Park Road; 11 am - 8 pm: Works of eminent artists. 

 Till September 4 at Gaganendra Pradarsasala; 2 pm - 8 pm: Paintings and sculptures by Contemporary Artist Group of Burdwan. 

 Till September 4 at Academy of Fine Arts, West Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: Graphic prints by Swapan Kumar Das. 

 DRAMA

 September 3 at Tapan Theatre; 6.30 pm: Charbak presents Chalo Patol Tuli. Drama amp; direction: Arindam Ganguly. 

 September 3 at G.D. Birla Sabhagar; 6.30 pm: Sanskriti Sagar and Spandan present Thaneer Thaneer (Hindi), produced by Padatik amp; Brainchild Theatre Production. Direction: Kunal Padhi. 

 September 4 at Uttam Mancha; 6.30 pm: Pancham Vaidic presents Rajnaitik Hatya. Direction: Saoli Mitra. 

 September 4 at Mukta Angan; 6.30 pm: Shouvanik will stage Washing Machine. Direction: Bimal Bandopadhayay 

 ANNIVERSARY

 September 3 at Rabindra Sadan; 5 pm: Shilpi Sansad observes Uttam Kumar?s 80th birth anniversary with luminaries from the field of music, literature and acting. The proceeds will go towards the building fund for less fortunate artistes. 

 September 3 at Uttam Mancha; 5.30 pm: Uttam Mancha celebrates Mahanayak Uttam Kumar?s 80th birth anniversary with a programme of songs and readings featuring leading personalities from the cultural world including Taslima Nasreen, Prosenjit, Supriya Devi, Gourab and Nabamita. A protion of the proceeds will go towards the welfare of Fakir Das, a well-known artiste of the yesteryear. Organised by Anwesha. 

 PERFORMING ARTS

 September 3 - 5 at Kala Kunj; 6 pm: Navaratna presents a classical music conference featuring Suchisree Roy (vocal) and Ranajit Sengupta (sarod) on Sept. 3; Harish Tiwari (vocal), and Sanjay Guha (sitar) and Indrayudh Bose (violin) duet on Sept. 4; and Shubhayu Sen Majumder (esraj) and Partho Bose (sitar) on Sept. 5. 

 September 4 at Rabindra Sadan; 5.30 pm: Samabeta presents Rabindra Sandhya. Participants include Swastika Mukhopadhyay, Abhirup Guha Thakurta, Shampa Kundu and Bikram Singh in solo recital of Tagore songs. Also, an audio-play based on Tagore?s Riddhi (Participants: Jagannath Basu and Urmimala Basu, with songs by Manoj Murali Nair and Manisha Murali Nair). Organised by Bhavna. 

 September 4 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Charuchetana presents an evening of Bengali songs by Srikanta Acharya and Lopamudra Mitra. 

 EXHIBITION

 September 3 amp; September 9 amp; 10 at 1/57B Dover Place, 2 pm - 7 pm: Gharoya?s exhibition of sarees, salwar-kameez tops, and lungi sets. 

 Till September 4 at Artisana, 13 Chowringhee Terrace, 1st floor; 10 am - 7.30 pm: Crafts Council of West Bengal presents Pooja, a collection of handicrafts and handcrafted textiles from weavers and dyers of all parts of India. Showcasing textiles like shibori saris, dupatta amp; yardage, kora silk, indigo-dyed cottons, kotah, gadwal, mangalgiri, chanderi, maheswari, bomkai and others. 

 Till September 3 at 5/1 Anil Moitra Road; 10 am - 6 pm: Weavers Studio presents Autumn celebrations in sunset hues, hand block prints on georgettes, crepes, tussars, sheer silk sarees, fabrics, outfits, dupattas, scarves and experimental surface textured textile scrolls. 

 Till September 4 at Olpadvala Hall, 52 Chowringhee Road; 10 am - 8 pm: An exhibition of used and discounted computers and their allied products. 

 talk

 September 3 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Shivananda Hall; 6 pm: Samiran Chandra Chakraborty will speak in Bengali on Veda Parikrama. 

 September 3 at Ramakrishna Vedanta Math, 19 A amp; B Raja Rajkrishna Street; 7 pm: Swami Paramatmananda will speak on Yog O Tahar Abhyas. 

 September 3 at Ramakrishna Math, Baranagar; 7 pm: Discourse on Life and teachings of Sadhoo Nagmahasay. Speaker: Swami Gyanabratananda. 

 September 4 at Advaita Ashrama, 5 Dehi Entally Road; 6 pm: Swami Govindananda will discuss Sri Sri Ramakrishna Kathamrita. 

 LECTURE

 September 3 at Netaji Bhawan, Sarat Bose Hall; 6.30 pm: Lalit Mansingh, former foreign secretary and Indian ambassador to the US, will deliver the Sarat Chandra Bose Memorial Lecture 2005. Topic: Future of Indo-US Relations. 

 SEMINAR

 September 3 at B.P. Poddar Hospital; 1 pm: Seminar on Dengue ? A Case Presentation and discussion on dengue management. Speaker: Internal medicine expert Dr N.S. Narayanan. 

 IN MEMORIAM

 September 4 amp; 5 at Sisir Mancha; September 6 at P-78 Lake Road: Baba Alauddin Sangeet Samaroh 2005 to commemorate his 33rd death anniversary. Organised by Baba Alauddin Smarak Samiti in collaboration with the state government?s department of information and cultural affairs. 

 READING

 September 4 at G.D. Birla Sabhagar; 11 am: Professor P. Lal reads Sanjaya?s report to Dhritarastra of the 8th day?s battle at Kuruksetra in which Bhima?s son Ghatotkacha routs the Kaurava army, and Bhima informs Arjuna of the slaughter of Arjuna?s son Iravat by the raksasa Alambusa, in the 293rd weekly Sunday session of his sloka-by-sloka English transcreation of Vyasa?s Mahabharata. 

